 bohemian New York to the west coast with significant implications for twentieth-century U.S. history and politics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aArtistszCaliforniazLos AngelesxHistoryy20th century. 0aCommunity lifezCaliforniazLos AngelesxHistoryy20th century. 0aCultural pluralismzCaliforniazLos AngelesxHistoryy20th century. 0aPolitical activistszCaliforniazLos AngelesxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / West (AK, CA, CO, HI, ID, MT, NV, UT, WY).2bisacsh  a20th century american culture.  a20th century american history.  a20th century american politics.  aartist.  aartistic expression.  abohemian.  acalifornia.  acivic.  acommunist party.  acultural studies.  adiplomacy.  aedendale.  agay men and women.  agay rights movement.  agender and sexuality.  agender studies.  ahistorical.  aidentity politics.  aleftists.  algbt community.  algbtqia.  alos angeles.  apolitical engagement.  apolitical.  arace in america.  arace relations.  aself expression.  asexual identity construction.  aunited states of america.  awartime los angeles.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094169440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520941694423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520941694/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles